         <div xml:id="main">
            <head type="incipit">
               <supplied reason="XTF-compatibility">7/6/93 ¶  ¶ By this week's post, noble friend, I am again sending you algae from Encounter Bay in South Australia, where they were collected by Miss Hussey. ¶  Admittedly the collection contains few r...</supplied>
            </head>
            <p rend="number" xml:lang="de">93.06.07</p>
            <p rend="correspondent" xml:lang="de">To Jacob Agardh</p>
            <p rend="location" xml:lang="de">Handskr. Avdl., Universitetsbibliotek, Lund, Sweden.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="de">7/6/93</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="de">
               <seg style="">
                  <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Durch diese Wochen-Post, edler Freund, sende ich Ihnen wieder Algen aus der Encounter-Bay (in Süd-Australien), wo solche von Miss Hussey gesammelt wurden. Freilich enthält die Sammlung wenig Seltenes und wohl kaum etwas Neues. Aber diese collection ist immerhin wichtig für </seg>
               <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">Localität</hi>
               </seg>
               <seg style="">, da manche Arten vom Süden des St Vincent's Golf noch nicht bekannt sein mögen. So sende ich denn selbst die </seg>
               <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">unvermeidliche</hi>
               </seg>
               <seg style=""> Ballia Brunonis, gewohnlich</seg>
               <seg style="">
                  <note xml:id="ftn1" type="footnote" n="1">
                     <p rend="Footnote"
                        style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <seg style="">
                           <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                           <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
                        </seg>gewöhnlich</p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
               <seg style="">
                  <name key="Plocamium">Plocamium</name>-Arten &amp;c Sie können selbige ja leicht in Ihrem Austausch verwerthen. </seg>
               <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">Eins</hi>
               </seg>
               <seg style=""> möchte ich aber doch bei dieser Gelegenheit erbitten, bei Quotation der Localität Miss Husseys Namen jedesmal zu nennen und eine etwa neue Alge dieser Sammlung Ihr zu widmen. Diese Dame ist an der Encounter-Bay wohnhaft; wenn sie also </seg>
               <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">ermuthigt</hi>
               </seg>
               <seg style=""> wird, mag sie sich auch mehr bemühen, nach Seltenheiten oder Neuheiten zu spähen dort.</seg>
            </p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="de">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Wer hat die Stelle unseres Freundes Schübeler jetzt in Christiania?</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="de">
               <seg style="">Sie ehrend, der Ihre</seg>
            </p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="de">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Ferd. von Mueller</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 10pt; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">7/6/93</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 10pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>By this week's post, noble friend, I am again sending you algae from Encounter Bay in South Australia, where they were collected by Miss Hussey.<note xml:id="ftn2" type="footnote" n="2">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>See also M to J. Agardh, 15 February 1893, for Hussey's first consignment from Encounter Bay, though M did not mention her by name.</p>
               </note> Admittedly the collection contains few rare things and I suppose hardly anything new. However, this collection is still important for <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">locality</hi>
               </seg>, since several species from south of St Vincents Gulf may not yet be known. So I am sending you even the <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">unavoidable</hi>
               </seg>
               <seg style="font-style: italic; ">
                  <name key="Ballia%20brunonis">Ballia brunonis</name>
               </seg>,<note xml:id="ftn3" type="footnote" n="3">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
                     <seg style="font-style: italic; ">Ballia brunonia</seg>? '<seg style="font-style: italic; ">Ballia callitricha</seg> is one of the commonest species of Rhodophyta on southern Australia coasts' (Electronic flora of South Australia, under <seg style="font-style: italic; ">Ballia callitriche</seg> of which <seg style="font-style: italic; ">B. brunonia</seg> is given as a synonym. URL: <ref target="http://www.flora.sa.gov.au/efsa/Marine_Benthic_Flora_SA/Part_IIIC/Ballia_callitricha.shtml"
                          rend="Internet%20link"
                          style="color: #0563c1; ">
                        <seg rend="Internet%20link" style="color: #0563c1; ">
                           <seg style="color: #0070c0; ">http://www.flora.sa.gov.au/efsa/Marine_Benthic_Flora_SA/Part_IIIC/Ballia_callitricha.shtm l</seg>
                        </seg>
                     </ref>(accessed 28 November 2018).</p>
               </note> common <seg style="font-style: italic; ">
                  <name key="Plocamium">Plocamium</name>
               </seg> species &amp;c. You can indeed easily use them in your exchanges. However, on this occasion I should like to request <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">one thing</hi>
               </seg>, to give Miss Hussey's name each time with the quotation of the locality and to dedicate a possible new alga of this collection to her. This lady is resident at Encounter Bay; thus if she is <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">encouraged</hi>
               </seg>, she might endeavour to look out even more for rarities or novelties there.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 10pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Who has the position of our friend Schübeler now in Christiania?<note xml:id="ftn4" type="footnote" n="4">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Now Oslo, Norway. </p>
               </note>
            </p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; font-size: 10pt; "
               xml:lang="en">Respectfully your</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; font-size: 10pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Ferd. von Mueller</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="plant%20names" xml:lang="en">
               <name key="Ballia%20brunonis">Ballia brunonis</name>
            </p>
            <p rend="plant%20names" xml:lang="en">
               <name key="Plocamium">Plocamium</name>
            </p>
         </div>
      </body>
